# CloudSentinel V0 — Event-Driven Self-Healing AWS Platform

This project deploys a production-ish AWS stack that:
- Runs a FastAPI service on EKS behind an internet-facing ALB
- Scales pods with HPA
- Scales nodes with Cluster Autoscaler
- Detects sustained high CPU on the node group ASG with a CloudWatch Alarm
- Triggers EventBridge -> Lambda auto-remediation (scales ASG desired capacity)
- Logs remediation actions to DynamoDB and notifies via SNS email

## Architecture (V0)
Users -> ALB (Ingress) -> EKS Service -> Pods
HPA scales pods, Cluster Autoscaler scales nodes
CloudWatch Alarm (ASG CPU) -> EventBridge -> Lambda
Lambda -> ASG scale + DynamoDB audit + SNS notification
RDS Postgres is provisioned (optional to wire into the app)